    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Stuart</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have been informally apprised that Mr.
                            Coppell, her Britannic Majesty’s acting consul at New Orleans, has
                            deemed it advisable to relinquish his official functions in consequence
                            of a letter addressed to him by Major General Butler, issued, it is
                            presumed, through some misapprehension. I do not think the facts of the
                            case justified General Butler in writing that letter. I will thank you,
                            therefore, to request that gentleman to resume his consular character,
                            the supposed cause of the abandonment of which is regretted. The
                            Secretary of War has been requested to issue proper orders upon the
                            subject to General Butler.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your very obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William Stuart, </hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
